  "text": "An isotope ratio mass spectrometer (POCOne; Otsuka Electronics Co. Ltd Osaka, Japan) was used to measure the 13 CO 2 / 12 CO 2 ratio of breath samples. The CO 2 production was assumed to be 300 mmol per square meter of body surface per hour. Body surface area was calculated from body mass and height. [CITATION_1] excretion, and half time represents the time taken for half the contents of the stomach to empty. Tmax and half time were calculated based on a standard analytical method. [CITATION_2] CA supplies blood flow to the stomach, liver and spleen, while the SMA supplies the entire small intestine, proximal portions of the colon and the pancreas. Simultaneous pulsed and echo Doppler ultrasound flowmetry (LOGIQ3, GE Healthcare, Piscataway, New Jersey, USA) were used to measure blood velocity and vessel diameters of CA and SMA, and cross-sectional gastric antral areas, as in previous studies.",
